# Architecture Boundaries

## Route groups and domain ownership

- `src/app/(coach)`: coach-facing flows and composition.
- `src/app/(client)`: client-facing flows with client navigation layout.
- `src/app/(training)`: immersive training flow without standard client nav.
- `src/app/(auth)`: authentication screens.

## Code placement

- Put business/domain logic in `src/features/<feature>/`.
- Put route-level fetching/composition in `src/app/**/queries.ts` and page/layout files.
- Put reusable UI primitives in `src/components/ui/`.
- Put cross-cutting infra/helpers in `src/lib/`.

## Data contracts

- Zod schemas belong in `src/features/<feature>/schemas.ts`.
- Feature domain types belong in `src/features/<feature>/types.ts`.
- DB-generated types live in `src/types/database.ts` and are never edited manually.

## Domain invariants

- `plans` are coach templates.
- `client_plans` are assigned copies.
- Assignment flows create copies, not mutable references.
